<TITLE> ACC gives away perks for anticorruption efforts </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 28 (bdnews24.com)The Anticorruption Commission Thursday rewarded 10 of its employees, including three directors, for their efforts in two high-profile corruption cases. ACC chairman Hasan Mashhud Chowdhury handed over the reward money at a modest ceremony. Three directorsFakir Firoz Ahmed, Nasreen Ara Surat Amin and Zakir Hossainreceived Tk 10,000 each for their contributions to the corruption case against former state minister Amanullah Aman and wife Sabera Aman who were jailed for 13 years and three years respectively. Deputy director Abdullah Al Zahid and investigating officer Jibon Krishno Roy were awarded Tk 30,000 each for their roles in the investigation, charge-sheet submission and charge-framing for the case. Three more employeesassistant inspector Zakir Hossain, senior assistant Abdul Khaleq and office assistant Rafiqul Islamwere given Tk 5,000 each for the same case. In the much-discussed corruption case against Giasuddin Al Mamun, assistant director ASM Akhtar Hamid Bhuiyan and assistant inspector Mahbubur Rahman were rewarded Tk 30,000 and Tk 10,000 respectively. Mamun was sentenced to three years in jail. Speaking to reporters after the ceremony, the ACC chairman said that such rewards show appreciation of good work, which can motivate others to perform likewise. "It will also bring more transparency to the actions of the ACC," said Chowdhury. bdnew
